<TITLE> Govt moves to ensure presidential mercy for jailed teachers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 22 (bdnews24.com) The government initiated a process to ensure mercy for three Dhaka University teachers immediately after a Dhaka court sentenced them to two years in jail Tuesday on charges of breaking emergency rule, an official said. President Iajuddin Ahmed is expected to grant mercy appeals in the shortest possible time, the official told bdnews24.com by phone on condition of anonymity because of the sensitivity of the issue. Secretary to the Chief Adviser's Office Kazi Aminul Islam has been assigned to expedite the process and carry the files to the president's office, the official said. bdnews24.
